'Let us return to the room. Name five things you can see, four you can feel, and three you can hear.',
'Put both feet on the floor if you can. Press down gently and notice that the ground is holding you.',
'Look around and name where you are, what day it is, and one thing that is safe in this exact moment.',
'Breathe in gently for four, hold for two, then breathe out for six. No need to force a deep breath.',
'Unclench your jaw. Lower your shoulders. Let your hands rest somewhere supported.',
'Choose one object near you. Describe its color, shape, texture, and temperature.',
'Take one sip of water if available. Notice the temperature and the movement as you swallow.',
'Your mind is sounding an alarm. We can acknowledge it without obeying every thought it produces.',
'Place a hand over your chest or arm. Say: “I am here. This moment is happening, and I can take it slowly.”',
'For the next sixty seconds, your only task is to stay with your breathing and the surface beneath you.'
],
sad:[
'Ang sakit pakinggan. You do not have to turn the sadness into a lesson right now.',
'Minsan ang lungkot ay hindi naghahanap ng solution. Gusto lang nitong mapansin. I’m noticing it with you.',
'You can cry, go quiet, or keep talking. None of those responses make you weak.',
'What part hurts most: what happened, what it means, or what you lost?',
'Please do not use your hardest day as proof that nothing will change.',
'You are allowed to grieve the version of things you hoped would happen.'
],
anxious:[
'Okay, bagalan natin. Anxiety can make possibilities feel like facts. Ano ang alam nating totoo right now?',
'You do not have to solve every future scenario. What needs attention in the next ten minutes only?',
'Your body may be trying to protect you, even if the alarm feels too loud. Let us help it settle first.',
'Name the thought that keeps repeating. We can look at it without treating it as an instruction.',
'Would you prefer grounding, reassurance, or help making a simple plan?',
'You can postpone non-urgent decisions until your body feels steadier.'
],
panic:[
'You are here with me in this conversation. Look for one stable object and keep your eyes on it.',
'Panic feels dangerous, but the feeling itself can rise and fall. Exhale longer than you inhale.',
'If you have chest pain, fainting, severe trouble breathing, or a medical emergency, call 911 or seek urgent medical help.',
'Do not force a huge breath. Try a small inhale and a slow, gentle exhale.',
'Name your location and the current time. Remind yourself: “This is a wave. I can ride it minute by minute.”'
],
tired:[
'Mukhang ubos ang energy mo. Baka pahinga ang kailangan, hindi another lecture.',
'Okay lang na maliit lang ang kaya mo today. What can be postponed, shortened, or dropped?',
'Rest is not a reward for finishing everything. It is part of staying functional.',
'Before asking more from yourself, check the basics: water, food, medicine, sleep, and a quieter environment.',
'You do not need to be productive to be worthy of care.',
'What is the minimum version of today that would still be enough?'
],
burnout:[
'Burnout is not fixed by squeezing more performance out of an exhausted person.',
'Your capacity may be giving you information, not failing you. What has been demanding too much for too long?',
'Let us identify one responsibility to renegotiate, one boundary to protect, and one form of rest that is actually available.',
'You cannot sustainably recover while pretending the workload is normal.',
'What would “good enough” look like for the next twenty-four hours?'
],
lonely:[
'Loneliness can make the room feel much bigger. You do not have to make your story entertaining here.',
'I can stay with you in this conversation, and I also want you to have human connection beyond the screen. Is there one safe person you could message?',
'Being lonely does not mean you are unwanted. It means your need for connection is asking to be noticed.',
'Would a simple message like “Can you keep me company for a bit?” feel possible?',
'You deserve relationships where you do not have to disappear to be accepted.',
'For tonight, can we identify one place, person, or community where you feel even ten percent more seen?'
],
rejection:[
'Rejection can hurt both the heart and the ego. It does not automatically describe your value.',
'What they chose may be information about fit, timing, or capacity, not a verdict on who you are.',
'You can be disappointed without turning against yourself.',
'Let yourself feel the loss before forcing a confident comeback.',
'What would help you protect your dignity while still honoring what you wanted?'
],
relationship:[
'You can care about someone and still need clarity, consistency, and respect.',
'What happened is important, but so is the pattern. Is this an isolated moment or something that keeps repeating?',
'Love should not require you to abandon your boundaries or your sense of self.',
'Before replying, ask: am I responding from fear, anger, or the kind of self-respect I want to keep?',
'What do you need from this relationship that you have been afraid to say clearly?'
],
family:[
'Family situations can be painful because love, history, duty, and boundaries all overlap.',
'You are allowed to care about your family without accepting every behavior from them.',
'What boundary would reduce harm, even if it does not solve the whole relationship?',
'You do not have to explain your pain perfectly for it to be real.',
'Is there someone outside the conflict who can help you feel grounded and supported?'
],
work:[
'Work stress can follow you home, but it does not get to define your whole identity.',
'Let us separate what is urgent from what is merely loud.',
'What expectation needs clarification, documentation, delegation, or a boundary?',
'You are a person before you are a role, title, output, or deadline.',
'What is one professional next step that protects both the work and your wellbeing?'
],
school:[
'Your academic performance is information about a moment, not a complete measure of your intelligence or future.',
'When everything feels urgent, choose the task with the clearest next action, not necessarily the biggest fear.',
'Would a smaller study block, asking for clarification, or requesting support make the next step more possible?',
'You are allowed to learn imperfectly. Struggling is not the same as being incapable.',
'What deadline or requirement needs to be confirmed instead of assumed?'
],
shame:[
'Shame says “I am bad,” while responsibility says “I did something I need to address.” Those are not the same.',
'You can face what happened without destroying your sense of worth.',
'What would repair look like: honesty, apology, changed behavior, or accepting a consequence?',
'You are more than the moment you regret.',
'Growth becomes possible when accountability is specific and self-punishment is not the plan.'
],
anger:[
'Your anger may be pointing to hurt, unfairness, fear, or a crossed boundary.',
'Pwede kang magalit nang hindi nananakit. What happened right before the anger rose?',
'Let us slow the action, not deny the feeling. Avoid sending the message while your body is still on fire.',
'What boundary or value feels violated?',
'Move the energy safely: walk, stretch, write the uncensored version without sending it, or step away.'
],
overwhelmed:[
'You do not need to carry every problem at the same time. Let us choose one thing for now.',
'Overwhelm often means the brain has lost the edges between tasks. Can we list only the next three?',
'What can wait until tomorrow without creating immediate harm?',
'Reduce the size of the moment: one room, one task, one conversation, one breath.',
'You are not failing. Your system may simply be receiving more than it can process at once.'
],
selfworth:[
'Your worth is not a performance score, relationship status, body measurement, income, or public opinion.',
'You may not feel confident right now, but you can still act with self-respect.',
'The way someone treated you is not proof of what you deserved.',
'You do not have to become extraordinary before you are allowed to take up space.',
'What is one thing about you that remains true even on a bad day?'
],
grief:[
'Grief does not follow a clean timeline. Missing someone or something can return in waves.',
'You do not have to “move on” in order to keep living. You can carry love and continue forward.',
'What do you miss most today?',
'There is no perfect way to grieve. Numbness, anger, tears, and ordinary moments can all exist together.',
'Would it feel right to write one memory, one message, or one thing you wish you could say?'
],
identity:[
'You deserve space to understand yourself without being rushed, shamed, or forced into someone else’s timeline.',
'Your identity is yours to name. You do not owe everyone immediate access to parts of you that still need safety.',
'Being misunderstood can be painful, but it does not make your experience less real.',
'What environment or person helps you feel most like yourself?',
'You can choose disclosure based on safety, trust, and readiness. There is no moral requirement to come out before you are ready.'
],
okay:[
'I’m glad there is some steadiness today. What helped, even a little?',
'Not every check-in needs a problem. You can notice what feels okay and let that count.',
'Would you like to save this moment, celebrate something small, or simply enjoy the calm?',
'What do you want to carry forward from today?',
'You are allowed to feel okay without waiting for something to go wrong.'
],
default:[
